OL,6,FMs Johnson told jurors that on July 8
OL,7,F2024 the "ever-present risk" to
OL,8,FKaylani became a "fatal reality".
OL,10,FShortly before 10.30pm, the defendants
OL,11,Fcalled emergency services saying
OL,12,FKaylani had stopped breathing.
OL,14,FWhen paramedics arrived, Merthoca
OL,15,Ffailed to inform them that Kaylani had
OL,16,Fbeen shaken, causing bleeding to the
OL,17,Fbrain, damage to her eyes and
OL,18,Ffractures to her tibia and ribs, the
OL,19,Fcourt was told.
